            <title>[SPARK-1610] Cast from BooleanType to NumericType should use exact type value.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-1610</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Cast from BooleanType to NumericType are all using Int value.&lt;br/&gt;
But it causes ClassCastException when the casted value is used by the following evaluation like the code below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;scala&amp;gt; import org.apache.spark.sql.catalyst._&lt;br/&gt;
import org.apache.spark.sql.catalyst._&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;scala&amp;gt; import types._&lt;br/&gt;
import types._&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;scala&amp;gt; import expressions._&lt;br/&gt;
import expressions._&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;scala&amp;gt; Add(Cast(Literal(true), ShortType), Literal(1.toShort)).eval()&lt;br/&gt;
java.lang.ClassCastException: java.lang.Integer cannot be cast to java.lang.Short&lt;br/&gt;
